  "title": "Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate with other department colleagues, customers, ship owners, agents and shipyards (SRM) with operation work plans.</li>\n  <li>Filling and compiling necessary documents or service reports to pass to next department.</li>\n  <li>Apply or renew various job-related permits; PSA/ Jurong Port/ Import-export permit, EPIC application and process.</li>\n  <li>Distribute Public Liability and WICA insurance policy documents to respective shipyards.</li>\n  <li>Manage company lorry vehicle for ad-hoc servicing &amp; delivery.</li>\n  <li>Assist in purchasing ad-hoc taxi e-voucher card for general works usage.</li>\n  <li>Support ad-hoc activities within scope of operations, operations related management systems, and innovation areas.</li>\n  <li>Apply and renewal of all operation work passes eg. shipyard pass – 2-way tag, HSE induction, shipyard passes and tags.</li>\n  <li>Apply visa and other necessary documents for overseas jobs.</li>\n  <li>Assist in organising OJT training for operations employees.</li>\n  <li>Supporting in activities related to NAV system, MES system, 5S (Printing of delivery orders, releasing RA, collecting/distributing of monthly 5S documents etc.).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>GCE `O' Level or Diploma.</li>\n  <li>Hands-on Individual with PC skills.</li>\n  <li>Adaptability, positive attitude and show willingness to learn.</li>\n  <li>Quick-witted and take initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills and customer service oriented attitude.</li>\n</ul>",
